message.content: cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.LG. The paper deals with question answering systems that require federating knowledge from a hybrid of heterogeneous data sources (structured and unstructured), which involves natural language processing (NLP), information retrieval (IR), artificial intelligence (AI), and database (DB) techniques. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning (ML) algorithms for relation extraction and schema annotation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the focus of the paper is on question answering systems, we consider cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the most likely category, followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
